An Elastic network interface is a logical networking component  in a VPC that represent 
a virtual  network card 

Details:
\_Description  : A description  of your network interface 
\_Subnet       : The subnet in which you want to  create a network interface
\_Interface type : 
                \_ENA  Elastic Network Adapter >> Standard high performance network interface used by most Ec2 instances
                \_EFA Elastic Fabric Adapter with ENA  >> EFA for hardware and ENA for capabilities (used for  HPC traffic via EFA  and Normal network Traffic via ENA)
                \_EFA only >>  only availabel on select specialized HPC or ML instances  

